Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: Suricata Won't Start
# Check Suricata status
sudo systemctl status suricata

# Check configuration syntax
sudo suricata -T -c /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml -v

# Check log files for errors
sudo tail -50 /var/log/suricata/suricata.log
Issue 2: No Alerts Generated
# Verify rules are loaded
sudo suricata --list-app-layer-protos

# Check if interface is correct
ip addr show

# Verify network traffic is being captured
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 -c 10
Issue 3: High CPU Usage
# Check Suricata process
top -p $(pgrep suricata)

# Optimize configuration for performance
sudo nano /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml
# Reduce threading or adjust buffer sizes
Issue 4: Log Files Growing Too Large
# Set up log rotation
sudo nano /etc/logrotate.d/suricata
Add the following configuration:

/var/log/suricata/*.log {
    daily
    missingok
    rotate 7
    compress
    notifempty
    create 640 root adm
    postrotate
        /bin/kill -HUP $(cat /var/run/suricata.pid 2>/dev/null) 2>/dev/null || true
    endscript
}
